description:
## 🧩 Problems to solve

We want to display suggested reviewers as a [dropdown](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/353087) on the code review sidebar. Suggested Reviewers (SR) is still an experimental feature and we want to ensure it does not adversely impact the existing reviewer lookup experience. The current response time of SR is not so great, that is > 100ms, therefore, we need to:

- Isolate SR API call to a separate endpoint
- Implement some level of cache to avoid any unnecessary call to the backend
- Prefetch suggested reviewers instead of when the users interact with the reviewer list

Contributed to https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/modelops/applied-ml/review-recommender/-/epics/3

## :bulb: Proposal

- Create a new GraphQL endpoint for `SuggestedReviewers`
- We can use the `mergeRequestReviewers` query as a guide

<details>
<summary>query</summary>

```graphql
query mergeRequestSuggestedReviewers($fullPath: ID!, $iid: String!) {
  workspace: project(fullPath: $fullPath) {
    __typename
    id
    issuable: mergeRequest(iid: $iid) {
      __typename
      id
      reviewers {
        nodes {
          ...User
          ...UserAvailability
          mergeRequestInteraction {
            canMerge
            canUpdate
            approved
            reviewed
            __typename
          }
          __typename
        }
        __typename
      }
      userPermissions {
        updateMergeRequest
        __typename
      }
    }
  }
}

fragment User on User {
  id
  avatarUrl
  name
  username
  webUrl
  __typename
}

fragment UserAvailability on User {
  status {
    availability
    __typename
  }
  __typename
}
```

</details>

<details>
<summary>response</summary>

```json
